              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "NGEN"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 Intense Neutron Generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons in 14 MeV region with a yield of about",
                "5E10 n/s. Deuteron beam energy was 255 keV and beam",
                "current was 350 uA. The solid T-Ti target used in the",
                "generator was about 2.19 mg/cm2 thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "72-HF-180",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.3508
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The natural hafnium foils of",
                "99.99% purity and 3 mm thickness were made into",
                "circular samples with a diameter of 2.0 cm. Each of",
                "them was sandwiched between two disks of thin niobium",
                " (99.99% purity and 1 mm thickness) of the same",
                "diameter, and was then wrapped in 1mm thick cadmium",
                "foil (purity better than 99.95%). Groups of samples",
                "were placed at 0, 45, 90 and 135 deg angles relative",
                "to the deuteron beam direction. The distances of",
                "samples from the center of the T-Ti target were about",
                "3-5 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A well-calibrated GEM-60P coaxial high-purity",
                "germanium (HPGe) detector (crystal diameter 70.1 mm,",
                "crystal length 72.3 mm) with a relative efficiency of",
                "about 68% and an energy resolution of 1.69 keV at",
                "1.332 MeV was used to measure the gamma-ray activities."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The irradiation time was 17 h."
              ]
            }
